<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Harlequin fetus refers to a rare autosomal recessive genetic disorder of skin formation. It is a severely disfiguring disorder involving thickened, ridged, and cracked skin forming horny plates over the entire body, distorting the facial features and constricting the digits. It is usually fatal in the first few days of life. It can be prenatally diagnosed in mothers who have a family history of the disease.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Despite the fact that most of them die shortly after birth, there are a few that live. <br>
<br>
(picture below, be forewarned)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.amorphousmedia.net/clients/wtfff.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
^^ That is a harlequin fetus that has survived 6 years, I believe he lives in Iran or something.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.btinternet.com/~stealthpredator/alien_child.mpeg">Living harlequin fetus baby (maybe NSFW)</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
My question is this. If you had a harlequin fetus child and were told that it could live a life of like 15 or more years, would you make the decision for the child to be killed while it was still a baby? <br>
<br>
Would you be a more loving person to let him/her live and suffer not only bodily pain, but the taunts, jeers and hate mongering? <br>
Or would you choose to have him/her killed before he/she could have the slightest notion of self knowing.<br>
<br>
