<br>
Our first daughter had Trisomy 13 (an extra chromosome 13, it controls certain development; Trisomy 21 is Down Syndrome), diagnosed at 4 months of my pregnancy.  We decided that, after feeling her move and been talking to her and loving her, we could not possibly abort.  She had a 1 in 4,000 chance of surviving birth.  After birth, a 1 in 4,000 chance of surviving her first month.  The longest recorded life for a Trisomy 13 baby is 6 years.  At a later stage, hi res sonogram showed she had double clef lips, club feet, croaked spine, her heart has a hole, and part of her brain was not developing.  It was grim.<br>
<br>
We soldiered on.  During the next 5 months, we talked to her.  She responded with punching and kicking.  We loved her even more.  She was ... IS our daughter.  We named her Audrey.  Oh and she kicked even more when I eat Korean pears.  She loved those.  <br>
<br>
At full term + 1 week, my contraction started, her little frail body could not handle the stress and died.<br>
<br>
You know, I would not have given up that 5 months for anything.  If she had survived, we would love her just the same.  I don't think we would have done it any different in this case.  Life is a miracle.  Life should be cherished.<br>
<br>
Just thought I'd share. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=328193"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/hibashirasakai/HibashiraNewHalfSize.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mausoleumthenecro>Mausoleum the Necro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Opinionated Asshole</span><br>  Posts: 513<br> <font color=#330000>(8/7/03 6:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=933.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: To let live or to euthanize? (kinda NSFW, no porn)</span><hr size=1> If you are asking would I have the child put to sleep after it had been born then again my answer is yes.<br>
